.DS_Store
.env
.env.*
!.env.example
build/
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
.pytest_cache/
.venv/
venv/
.idea/
*.log

# RAG VDB outputs (chroma sqlite + bm25 pickle + metadata) — large, regenerable.
play/*/vdb/
play/qa_assets/vdb/

# Evaluation run artifacts (per-run result/samples + cross-run index) — regenerable from `python -m evals score/run`.
play/evals/runs/

# agent_sft Phase 2 mined data — local smoke / scratch artifacts only; final 1k batches are committed below.
play/agent_sft/data/triples/runs/
play/agent_sft/data/triples/*.jsonl
# But keep the final Phase 2 deliverables in repo (250 envelopes per model + derived jsonl):
!play/agent_sft/data/triples/*_1k.jsonl

# agent_sft Phase 3 training artifacts policy (DECISIONS §5):
# - Smoke run (throwaway): ignored entirely.
# - Per-run `.data/` symlink dirs (data plumbing): ignored.
# - All adapter `.safetensors` ignored by default — except the Phase 4 entry adapter
#   at runs/sweeps/iters/200/ which is the recommended config from sweep (DECISIONS §5)
#   and unblocks Phase 4 fuse on a fresh checkout.
# - All analysis artifacts (`REPORT.md`, `results.json`, per-run `train.log` /
#   `train_metrics.json` / `eval_smoke.json`, `adapter_config.json`) committed for
#   cross-machine reproducibility + traceability (~100 KB total).
play/agent_sft/train/runs/smoke/
play/agent_sft/train/runs/sweeps/**/.data/
play/agent_sft/train/runs/sweeps/**/*.safetensors
!play/agent_sft/train/runs/sweeps/iters/200/adapters.safetensors
# Override the global `*.log` rule (top of this file) for sweep logs — small text artifacts,
# useful for post-mortem of train + eval timing / per-iter loss curve / divergence checks.
!play/agent_sft/train/runs/sweeps/sweep.log
!play/agent_sft/train/runs/sweeps/**/*.log

# agent_sft Phase 4 deploy artifacts: ~18 GB intermediates (fused-mlx-fp16 + f16 gguf + q4 gguf)
# already covered by the top-level `build/` rule, listed explicitly for grep-ability.
play/agent_sft/deploy/build/
